---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import DashboardShell from "@/components/dashboard/DashboardShell";
---

<BaseLayout>
	<div class="section gap-y-16 py-24">
		<!-- Hero -->
		<div class="col-span-full px-4 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
			<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-4">Sign Up & Connect</h1>
			<p class="text-lg text-white/70 mb-6">
				This is your entry point into ChainFlow's network capital protocol. Connect or create a smart wallet using Thirdweb, then let the network score your on-chain activity and scale your capital line from 50K toward 1M.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Sign up & connect card + explainer -->
		<div class="col-span-full px-4 max-w-6xl mx-auto space-y-8">
			<div class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-white/15 bg-black/40 backdrop-blur">
				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Create or connect your smart wallet</h2>
				<p class="text-sm text-white/70 mb-5">
					Use the connect modal to sign up with email, social, or an existing wallet. Behind the scenes, a smart account is created for you on the Paxeer stack.
				</p>
				<div class="flex justify-center">
					<DashboardShell client:only="react" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
				<div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">2. How the network uses your wallet</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-white/70">
						Once connected, the network risk engine observes this wallet: trades, liquidity, app interactions, and more. Those signals drive your capital line, guardrails, and payout windows.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">3. Use it anywhere on-chain</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-white/70">
						After connecting, you can use this wallet across apps, trading venues, and liquidity pools. The protocol will handle risk scoring, capital allocation, and payout eligibility on your behalf.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
